com.storytron.swat

Class Swat

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.swat.Swat

  • public final class Swat
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the root of the Swat tool application.

    When instantiating Swat, saving properties to disk must be done in a shutdown hook registered by the programmer.

    The reaction to the CMD-Q event is implemented in the quit() method.

    The StorytellerRemote.logout(String) is called by a shutdown hook registered by the Swat() constructor.

    Swat is started from the SwatMain class, which sets some system properties needed before the jvm loads the awt classes.
